weird. He was also annoyed because they wouldn’t let him speak.</p> <p><strong>&lt;Question&gt; Are Nicolson.mp and his colleagues robots?</strong> No. No, they’re not.</p> <p><strong>&lt;Question&gt; Is it weird to be a robot? </strong>That depends on your point of view. Woodcock’s Labour party is currently a total mess because it can’t agree on anything. Its leader never followed instructions from past leaders and is now struggling to convince the rest to take instructions from him. Basically, Woodcock wants to make it look as if the SNP are all scheming hypocrites for showing discipline, whereas Labour are principled politicians.</p> <p><strong>&lt;SNP hypocrisy&gt; and &lt;Labour mess&gt; do not mutually exclude. </strong>No. I suppose you’re right there.</p> <p><strong>&lt;Say&gt;</strong> “I’m sorry Dave, I’m afraid I can’t do that.”</p> <p><strong>&lt;/Say&gt; </strong>“Exterminate English hegemony!”</p>","internalOctopusCode":"11016586","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-11-26T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2413654","internalRevision":"44","internalContentCode":"458435167","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"Labour’s John Woodcock was questioned over his language in the Commons after accusing SNP MPs of being a bunch of androids. &lt;ENGAGE PASS NOTES SEQUENCE&gt;","allowUgc":"false","headline":"Why ‘robot’ is parliament's new favourite insult","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2015-11-25T16:28:09Z","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/2aee7387b8724ea9e7f9da5bbd4ad8a13024715b/0_0_5315_3188/140.jpg","isPremoderated":"false","internalComposerCode":"5655da36e4b090c9def04805","newspaperPageNumber":"3","commentCloseDate":"2015-11-28T16:30:00Z","standfirst":"<p>Labour’s John Woodcock was questioned over his language in the Commons after accusing SNP MPs of being a bunch of androids. &lt;ENGAGE PASS NOTES SEQUENCE&gt;</p>","creationDate":"2015-11-25T15:56:38Z","show