tained for stability’s sake</a>.</p> <p><strong>Who claims that? </strong>Divorce lawyers.</p> <p><strong>Well, they would, wouldn’t they? </strong>Probably. According to a survey by the family lawyers’ group Resolution, eight out of 10 children of divorced parents believe a split is preferable to an intact but unhappy marriage.</p> <p><strong>Remind me how much a divorce costs again. </strong>Between £3,000 and £30,000, depending on how acrimonious. Much more if you’re rich.</p> <p><strong>In that case, I’d rather draw a line down the middle of the house and wait for death’s sweet release. </strong>That’s the spirit – stay positive.</p> <p><strong>Do say:</strong> “Happy 21st, darling! Your father and I have some news.”</p> <p><strong>Don’t say:</strong> “We’ve divided up the books and paintings amicably. If only there were some kind of professional arbiter who could help us separate the silver.”</p>","internalOctopusCode":"11011557","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-11-25T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2412827","internalRevision":"93","internalContentCode":"458428575","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"Divorce rates are dropping across the board – except for one age group, who seem to be splitting up as soon as their children are out of the door","allowUgc":"false","headline":"Meet the silver separators: why over-50s top the divorce charts","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2015-11-24T16:22:44Z","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/6b8f88f33a20e9dfd1fc933208692e8f3bf00ee5/0_289_4368_2620/140.jpg","isPremoderated":"false","internalComposerCode":"56547cdde4b048c187b485c2","newspaperPageNumber":"3","commentCloseDate":"2015-11-27T16:15:00Z","standfirst":"<p>Divorce rates are dropping across the board – except for one age group, who seem to be splitting up as soon as their children are out of the door</p>","creationDate":"2015-11-24T15:06:05Z","showInRelatedContent":"